Drummond has also appeared in other works. In 1983 Jack Smithers wrote the spoof ''Combined Forces'',<ref name="BL: Combined forces" />{{efn|Subtitled ''being the latter-day adventures of Maj-Gen Sir Richard Hannay, Captain Hugh 'Bulldog' Drummond and Berry and Co.''}} and in 1990 [[Kim Newman]]—under the name Jack Yeovil—wrote the short story "Pitbull Brittan", which features Drummond.{{sfn|Hardy|1997|p=117}}

===Short stories===
These short stories are all by McNeile.

