The '''Royal Carriages Museum''' is located at the [[Cairo Citadel|Citadel]] in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]], in front of Suleiman Pasha Mosque. The museum was inaugurated in 1983, then it was re-inaugurated after its renovation in 2013.

It houses a collection of unique Royal Carriages attributed to different historical periods, from the reign of Khedive Ismail until the reign of King Farouk, in addition to other collection of unique antiques related to the carriages.

