{{third-party|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox Book | name = Gray's Anatomy for Students | title_orig = | translator = | image = Gray's Anatomy for Students.jpg | image_caption = | author = Richard Drake, A. Wayne Vogl, Adam W. M. Mitchell | illustrator = Richard Tibbitts and Paul Richardson | cover_artist = | country = [[England]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = [[Human anatomy]] | genre = | publisher = [[Churchill Livingstone]] | pub_date = Oct 2004 | media_type = | pages = 1150 | isbn = 978-0-443-06612-2 | oclc = | preceded_by = [[Gray's Anatomy]] | followed_by = }}
'''''Gray's Anatomy for Students''''' is an anatomy textbook inspired by the famous ''[[Gray's Anatomy]]'' (Grey's Anatomy) and aimed primarily at [[medical students]]. The textbook has been praised for its innovative illustration style, which emphasizes clarity and a conceptual approach to learning.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Grays-Anatomy-Students-Richard-Drake/dp/0443066124 |publisher=Amazon |title=''Gray's Anatomy for Students: with Student Consult Online Access, 1e''}}</ref> The text aims to display the basic concepts for chiropractic, dental, medical, and physical therapy students.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sajko|first=Sandy S.|date=2006-12|title=Gray’s Anatomy for Student’s|journal=The Journal of the Canadian Chiropractic Association|volume=50|issue=4|pages=290|issn=0008-3194|pmc=1840002}}</ref>
''Gray's Anatomy'' was used as the major reference, both for the text and the illustrations.<ref>''Gray's Anatomy for Students'', page xi, paragraph 3.</ref>
