[[Category:Anatomy books]] [[Category:Medical manuals]] [[Category:Gray's Anatomy]]
{{med-book-stub}}

{{italictitle}}
'''''Help in the Winter''''' ({{lang-sl|Zimska pomoč}}) was a [[Slovene language|Slovene]] almanac published in 1944<ref name="Luthar2008">{{cite book|author=Oto Luthar|title=The Land Between: A History of Slovenia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G9tDboBJ70EC&pg=PA441|year=2008|publisher=Peter Lang|isbn=978-3-631-57011-1|pages=441–442}}</ref> by 110 [[anticommunism|anticommunist]] authors in protest against the [[Liberation Front of the Slovene Nation|Slovene Liberation Front]]'s policy of [[cultural silence]]. Whereas the authors were gathered under the guise of charitable activity, later, their work was claimed to be a direct and effective opposition to the cultural silence.<ref name="Luthar2008" /> The authors who published the almanac did not join the [[Slovene Partisans|Partisan movement]].<ref name="KlemenčičŽagar2004">{{cite book|author1=Matjaž Klemenčič|author2=Mitja Žagar|title=The former Yugoslavia's diverse peoples: a reference sourcebook|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ORSMBFwjAKcC&pg=PA180|accessdate=22 February 2012|year=2004|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-57607-294-3|page=180}}</ref>

