The '''Indian Super League Golden Boot''' is an annual association football award presented to the leading goalscorer in the Indian Super League.
The award in 2014 was sponsored by '''[[Maruti Suzuki]]''' and the award was hence called Alto K10 Indian Super League Golden Boot.<ref name=top>{{cite news |title=HEROISL: EX-LEICESTER STRIKER HUME NAMED PLAYER OF THE ISL, ELANO LANDS GOLDEN BOOT |url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/heroisl-ex-leicester-striker-hume-named-player-isl-elano-lands-golden-boot-4054435#.VJap7sAA |date=December 2014 |accessdate=21 December 2014 |publisher=Goal.com }}</ref>
The Indian Super League was founded in 2014 and the league consisted of 8 teams representing different cities.
The first Indian Super League golden boot was won by [[Elano]] of [[Chennaiyin FC]] in 2014 after he finished as the top scorer with 8 goals.<ref name>{{cite news |title=Elano wins Golden Boot for ISL exploits with Chennaiyin |url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/news/7083/isl/2014/12/20/7246022/elano-wins-golden-boot-for-isl-exploits-with-chennaiyin |date=December 2014 |accessdate=21 December 2014 |publisher=Goal.com }}</ref>
