{{italic title}}

'''''Post-Balzac''''' is a bronze sculpture by [[Judith Shea]] created in 1991 in an edition of three copies.

It was exhibited at the [[White House]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://clinton2.nara.gov/WH/Tours/Garden_Exhibit5/exhibit.html|title=Twentieth Century American Sculpture - Exhibit V|website=clinton2.nara.gov|accessdate=6 September 2018}}</ref> and the John and Mary Pappajohn Sculpture Park.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flickriver.com/photos/hanneorla/5334401190/|title=Judith Shea 'Post Balzac', 1990, Western Gateway Center, John and Mary Pappajohn Sculpture Park, Des Moines, Iowa - a photo on Flickriver|website=www.flickriver.com|accessdate=6 September 2018}}</ref>

